Residents pondering their next move after nine sheep were killed by a wild animal injuring Eight at Kiamunyeki, Lanet in Nakuru County on November 22, 2021 [Harun Wathari, Standard]  A family in Kiamunyeki area of Nakuru County lost nine sheep after a wild animal entered their home and attacked livestock.  The wild animal that attacked at around 3.30am yesterday, also critically injured five sheep and left four with minor injuries.  Dundori Division Assistant County Commissioner Henry Kirua, confirmed the incident.  “We have forwarded the report to the Kenya Wildlife Service for further action,” said Kirua. “There is a dangerous animal on the loose around this area and the residents must be careful. They should also report if they have any information that would be of help.”  Justice delayed for teen raped by neighbour  Police impound 20,000 litres of untaxed ethanol  I'll defend my seat next year, says Nakuru Governor Kinyanjui  Nakuru households set to benefit from Sh500 million emergency water program      Serikali ya kaunti ya Nakuru yatoa pendekezo la kuzuia uvuvi katika ziwa Naivasha  KENHA urges Kenyans plying the Nairobi-Nakuru highway to use alternative routes  Tussle over the ownership of land in Ngongogeri, Nakuru threatening peace amongst disputing parties By Robert Amalemba | 4 hours ago By Jacob Ng'etich | 4 hours ago By Antony Gitonga | 4 hours ago By James Munyeki | 4 hours ago Speaker Justin Muturi on Uhuru, Raila 'secret pact'